 Job Description
  Overview/Purpose
 CitizenNet Campaign Managers at Cond√© Nast drive the success of social marketing initiatives for the biggest brands in Entertainment, Publishing, CPG, and more. Effectively implement client strategy on social, and create and execute their campaigns. Learn key marketing initiatives with hands-on experience from multiple verticals, and gain from experience of working at Cond√© Nast, one of the most renowned media companies in the world.
 Primary Responsibilities
 Media Planning, Optimization & Measurement
 Use CitizenNet software and social platforms to plan and implement strategies and audience targeting for clients
 Build campaigns on Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, Pinterest, Snapchat, Twitter, etc. to achieve client goals
 Day-to-day campaign management and performance monitoring with high attention to detail
 Campaign optimization towards client goals
 Creation of reporting dashboards and insights development
 Assume ownership on high priority campaign planning, execution, and analysis projects
 Direct client communication in response to campaign management and performance
 Product
 Provide vital feedback to the CitizenNet product team to drive innovation and efficiency
 Team
 Work in a collaborative environment where insights, recommendations, and ideas are welcome
 Contribute to the growth and success of your team and clientbase through ideation and brainstorming. This can include, but not limited to: troubleshooting, platform research, and maintaining clear communication with your team.
 As a contributor to employee success and culture, participate in new employee onboarding and training
 Desired Skills and Qualifications
 We are looking for candidates who are excited about technology, data analysis, social media, and advertising. Candidates must be motivated to succeed in a fast-paced and growing environment. A willingness to adopt new technologies and trends is extremely important for this position. Our candidates must be proficient in time management with the ability to manage multiple projects at once, balancing various goals and parameters.
 Minimum requirements
 BA/BS degree
 1-2 years experience managing paid social campaigns with campaign budgets exceeding $100K
 Fluency in digital advertising concepts and paid social
 Previous use of social media platforms for marketing and/or advertising
 Exceptional attention to detail and strong organization skills
 Ability to multi-task and manage projects
 Strong communication skills and a dedicated team player
 Excel/Powerpoint/Keynote proficiency
 Experience in live events is a plus
 Experience with SQL, Python and data management platforms a plus
